# Rulebook to Codebase Mapping

This document provides an overview of how the game's rulebook and progression phases are directly implemented in the codebase. It is structured chronologically, following the flow of a standard game or campaign. Use this as a reference when editing game rules or diagnosing bugs.

---

## 1. Game Setup & Deckbuilding
Before a match begins, players assemble their decks and the game engine initializes the state.

**Supporting Code:**
- **Deckbuilding Logic:** `src/ui/DeckBuilderUI.js`
  - Handles the "drafting" and "modify deck" UI flows (`buildDeck`, `_showDraftScreen`, `_showModifyScreen`).
- **Campaign Rules & Storage:** `src/campaign/WarCampaignData.js` / `src/campaign/CampaignData.js`
  - Defines round rules, deck sizes, and VP rewards (e.g., `WAR_ROUNDS_MULTI`, `WAR_ROUNDS_2P`).
- **Game Initialization:** `src/engine/GameController.js` (`setupGame`)
  - Takes the selected decks/configs, filters them into CardInstances using `src/engine/CardDatabase.js`, and loads them into `src/engine/GameState.js`.
- **UI Entry Point:** `src/ui/GameUI.js` (`showMenu`, `showRegionSelect`, `startGame`) and `src/main.js` (`init`).

---

## 2. Pre-Game: Landmark Placement & Mulligan
Before the first turn, players can place a free Landmark and mulligan their opening hand.

**Supporting Code:**
- **Initial Draw:** `src/engine/TurnManager.js` (`startGame`)
  - Shuffles decks and deals 5 cards to Player 1, 6 cards to Player 2+.
- **Pre-game Landmark Placement:** `src/ui/GameUI.js` (`showLandmarkSelect`)
  - Prompts the user to select a Landmark from their deck and a target zone. Bypasses normal mana costs.
- **Mulligan UX:** `src/ui/GameUI.js` (`showMulliganScreen`)
  - Handles the UI for selecting which cards to replace.
- **Mulligan Logic:** `src/engine/TurnManager.js` (`performMulligan`, `checkMulliganComplete`)
  - Shuffles selected cards back into the deck, draws replacements, and advances to the first turn via `startFirstTurn()`.

